cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on facial landmark detection in motion-blurred videos, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a structure predictor, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the performance of their proposed framework, which involves evaluating the accuracy of the landmark detection algorithm, making cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of motion blur, which is related to image processing and graphics, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category.
